        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Gumbel (or Smallest Extreme Value (SEV) or the Smallest Extreme\nValue Type I) distribution is one of a class of Generalized Extreme\nValue (GEV) distributions used in modeling extreme value problems.\nThe Gumbel is a special case of the Extreme Value Type I distribution\nfor maximums from distributions with \"exponential-like\" tails."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The probability density for the Gumbel distribution is"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "p(x) = \\frac{e^{-(x - \\mu)/ \\beta}}{\\beta} e^{ -e^{-(x - \\mu)/ \\beta}},"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "where "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\mu"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the mode, a location parameter, and\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\beta"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the scale parameter."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Gumbel (named for German mathematician Emil Julius Gumbel) was used\nvery early in the hydrology literature, for modeling the occurrence of\nflood events. It is also used for modeling maximum wind speed and\nrainfall rates.  It is a \"fat-tailed\" distribution - the probability of\nan event in the tail of the distribution is larger than if one used a\nGaussian, hence the surprisingly frequent occurrence of 100-year\nfloods. Floods were initially modeled as a Gaussian process, which\nunderestimated the frequency of extreme events."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "It is one of a class of extreme value distributions, the Generalized\nExtreme Value (GEV) distributions, which also includes the Weibull and\nFrechet."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The function has a mean of "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\mu + 0.57721\\beta"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and a variance\nof "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\frac{\\pi^2}{6}\\beta^2"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "1\n\nGumbel, E. J., \"Statistics of Extremes,\"\nNew York: Columbia University Press, 1958.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "2\n\nReiss, R.-D. and Thomas, M., \"Statistical Analysis of Extreme\nValues from Insurance, Finance, Hydrology and Other Fields,\"\nBasel: Birkhauser Verlag, 2001.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "References"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "mu, beta = 0, 0.1 # location and scale"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "s = we.random.gumbel(mu, beta, 1000)"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Display the histogram of the samples, along with\nthe probability density function:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "count, bins, ignored = plt.hist(s, 30, density=True)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.plot(bins, (1/beta)*we.exp(-(bins - mu)/beta)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "* we.exp( -we.exp( -(bins - mu) /beta) ),"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "linewidth=2, color='r')"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.show()"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Show how an extreme value distribution can arise from a Gaussian process\nand compare to a Gaussian:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "means = []"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "maxima = []"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "for i in range(0,1000) :"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "a = we.random.normal(mu, beta, 1000)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "means.append(a.mean())"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "maxima.append(a.max())"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "count, bins, ignored = plt.hist(maxima, 30, density=True)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "beta = we.std(maxima) * we.sqrt(6) / we.pi"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "mu = we.mean(maxima) - 0.57721*beta"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.plot(bins, (1/beta)*we.exp(-(bins - mu)/beta)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "* we.exp(-we.exp(-(bins - mu)/beta)),"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "linewidth=2, color='r')"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.plot(bins, 1/(beta * we.sqrt(2 * we.pi))"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "* we.exp(-(bins - mu)**2 / (2 * beta**2)),"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "linewidth=2, color='g')"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.show()"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Examples"
      }
